CJD (new var.) - UK: 1985-1998 981013203955
Date: Fri 4 Dec 1998 17:42:06 -0500
From: "Robert A. LaBudde" <ral@lcfltd.com>
Source: Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy <BSE-L@RZ.UNI-KARLSRUHE.DE>

Per the website at:
http://www.cjd.ed.ac.uk/figures.htm
The latest info on nvCJD (as of 30 Sep 1998, per the site) is:
New Variant CJD
------------------
At present there are 29 confirmed cases and one probable case of the new
variant of CJD in the UK known to the CJD surveillance unit. Ten of
these cases are as reported by Will et al in the Lancet article of 6 Apr
1996.
Another case of this variant form of CJD has been reported in France by
Chazot et al (Lancet, 27 Apr 1996).
CJD Figures
------------
These figures show the number of suspect cases referred to the CJD
surveillance unit in Edinburgh, and the number of deaths of definite and
probable cases in the UK, up to 30 Sep 1998. Full details of our
statistics can be found in our Sixth Annual Report published on 22 Apr
1998.
Deaths of definite and probable cases in the UK:
Year Referrals Sp. Iat. Fam. GSS nv Total@
1990 [53 28 5 0 0 - 33
1991 75 32 1 3 0 - 36
1992 96 43 2 5 1 - 51
1993 78 38 4 2 2 - 46
1994 116 51 1 4 3 - 59
1995 87 35 4 2 3 3 47
1996 134 41 4 2 4 10 61
1997 158 56 6 4 1 10 77
1998* 97 20 0 1 0 6 27
@ Sp. = sporadic, Iat. = iatrogenic, Fam. = familial, nv = nvCJD
* To 30 Sept 1998.
*** Because of one death since 30 Sept 1998, the present total number
of definite and probable [UK cases of nvCJD = 30.
